Title: Gates of Edengrove
Description: Clear Dryads in the Crescent Window, and clear Blight Fiends at the Blisteroot. Then report back to Survivalist Ellwood in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, that’s the question on everyone’s minds, isn’t it? Edengrove is a place of vast natural magic, the Angry Earth’s ancient home. \n\nIf the Blight can spread this fast, even here, maybe nothing can stop it.
InProgressResponse: The Angry Earth Dryads are deadly enough already, but the Blight makes them even worse.\n\nPlease, try to come back in one piece.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, thank you, these will do nicely. \n\nIt feels odd, trying to help the Angry Earth. My old instructor would have told me off for sympathizing with the enemy, instead of taking advantage of their weakness.

Title: Good For What Ails You
Description: Craft or procure a Concentrated Blight Tincture, and then report back to Survivalist Ellwood in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I thought so too. Some of the Dryads seemed amiable, but after the Blight emerged, communication broke down.\n\n If we purge the Blight from the Grove, they might come around… I hope.
InProgressResponse: If you do not have the resources to craft a Blight Tincture, you'll have to gather or purchase them from the Trading Post.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, yes. Well done! This can save you from great suffering.\n\nMore than a few have limped into the outpost covered in red fungus. They beg for death even as it saps away their strength.

Title: Gum in the Works
Description: Sabotage the Corrupted miners in the Profane Seam by raiding their supplies and thinning their numbers. Then report back to Warden Ducquet in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: We've been waiting for the right opportunity, of course. Like your arrival.\n\nThis would seem to be the right moment, if you're willing to lead the charge.
InProgressResponse: Have you been to the Profane Seam yet? The fiends think that hiding among the crags will keep them safe. \n\nThey'll soon know better, won't they?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Success! You're quite the warrior, aren't you? Assaulting their camps and striking without mercy. Well done!  \n\nPerhaps that will slow their supply chain from Great Cleave and Shattered Mountain, as well.

Title: Gutting the Guard, Firing the Foreman
Description: Destroy Elite Guard Philippe and Foreman Harold in the mines in the Profane Seam. Then report back to Warden Ducquet in Edengrove.
PlayerPrompt: "That sounds like a plan to me."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Perfect. The Rangers have identified the commanders.\n\nElite Guard Philippe and Foreman Robertson - destroy that pair, and we'll have all the Corrupted in Edengrove running scared.
InProgressResponse: The Rangers say Philippe and Robertson are running operations from within the mine. Good luck, Warden.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Cut off the head and the body will fall! Dealing with those two will bring their operations to a standstill. \n\nThat should have the Corrupted questioning their strategy here.

Title: Northeast of Eden
Description: Meet Survivalist Ellwood in Edengrove's northeast Outpost.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: He was in quite a hurry. His mission to combat the Blight drew him to the northeast Outpost.\n\nHe asked if you would meet him there. I told him I would relay the message, and so I have.
InProgressResponse: The journey northeast will be a difficult one. That I can assure you.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, brave one, I see you have made the journey safely. I am glad to see your face.\n\nForgive my rush, but I believe that here in the northeast, we will find the answers we seek.

Title: Fading Lights
Description: Investigate the Ancient Guardians and their movements in the Primal Lochan. Then report back to Ranger Wardell in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Well, in most territories, they are charged with simply securing certain ruins.\n\nHere, however, it seems they are charged with securing all of Edengrove.
InProgressResponse: It seems there was a time when the Ancients considered this territory to be exclusively theirs.\n\nThe Guardians still seem dead-set on enforcing this mandate.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, there you are. I hope you dealt them a blow from which they won't soon recover.\n\nThe last thing we need right now is to fall under attack from the Ancient Guardians.

Title: Azure Tears
Description: Collect Wyrdwood Tears from the Dryad soldiers in the Wyrdwood Twists area. Then report back to Ranger Wardell in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I do, so listen well. Edengrove is abundant in wyrdwood trees, which have a beautiful glow. \n\nThe sap from such trees can be refined into what we call Wyrdwood Tears - sacred to the Rangers.
InProgressResponse: Collecting the Tears will support the Rangers out in the wilds. \n\nYou're doing us a significant favor here.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, these Tears have saved my life more than once, when I was alone in the wilds.\n\nThese will be much appreciated by the other Rangers, as well. We are, again, in your debt.

Title: A Pox On Thee
Description: Defeat Denman at the top of Nettlevex tower, and bring his remains to Ellwood in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There is a tower known as Nettlevex. The tower itself has become Blighted, but some within have resisted. \n\nThere's one in particular known as the "Denman." Bring me samples of its vines if you can.
InProgressResponse: The tower is a rough gauntlet, and the Dryads are formidable. \n\nTake care in your climb, Denman will be the strongest of the lot.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, indeed, a fine specimen. The wood and earth that compose Denman's vines flow thick with old azoth.\n\nThis supports my theory. Did you know Edengrove is the source of all Angry Earth on Aeternum?

Title: Strength of the Earth
Description: Go to the ruins of Litheltop and investigate the hidden Blight at its heart. Then report back to Survivalist Ellwood in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I'm not sure yet. There's a fresh outbreak of Blight deep in Elysian Falls, at Litheltop.\n\nThe Dryads there are old and experienced, and they may be able to resist it… for now.
InProgressResponse: We aren't the Dryads' true enemy, but they don't make that distinction. \n\nYou will undoubtedly have to fight them when you go to collect those Blight samples.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So the Dryads at Litheltop have held out so far? That's good. Supports my theory.\n\nLet’s see these fresh Blight samples then… hmmm. Oh. This one is old growth, and yet still infected…

Title: Diseased Migration
Description: Go to the Blightcrown to investigate the movement of the Blight beyond Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, that’s my theory! \n\nBlight is apparently a threat to all life forms, but what if that’s the entire point? What if it's actually a mechanism of self-defense?
InProgressResponse: Beyond the Pass is the the Shattered Mountain, where I'm told the Corrupted have amassed in great numbers. \n\nIf you go there, go prepared.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Then you've confirmed it, have you? The Blight extends towards the Shattered Mountain.\n\nThe final question remains only, how is the Blight affecting the Corrupted?

Title: Anguine Anguish (Expedition)
Description: Defeat the Greenskeeper in the Garden of Genesis. Then report back to Survivalist Wardell in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, it is the sacred nursery for all Angry Earth, and when young, they are most vulnerable.\n\nIf we help protect their young in the Garden, we may yet forge some understanding.
InProgressResponse: The Greenskeeper is not only a threat to the Garden, but to all of Aeternum. \n\nHe is but one of the many ways the Blight has manifested. We must release the Garden from his grip.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah! Then the Greensman is no more? His scourge will take ages to heal, but at least it has begun.\n\nThanks to you, brave one, there is hope. The young will sprout again, and cycle of the earth will continue.

Title: Threat of Life (Elite)
Description: Watcher Lin has asked you to find a key to enter Zygoramet's Grove and destroy the dangerous creature inside. Then report back to Watcher Lin in Edengrove.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There was a naturalist here a few decades ago who disappeared after falling to the Blight.\n\nShe had discovered that there is an Angry Earth specimen here capable of replicating itself an infinite number of times... in the blink of an eye!
InProgressResponse: I am not exaggerating. The creature inside Zygoramet's Grove will consume us all.\n\nYou must get a key to enter the Grove and destroy it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, you've returned? The creature is slain then? Damn, you're the first who's actually believed me. \n\nPeople might not realize it, but we're all a lot safer now.

Title: Down Reekwater Way
Description: Speak to Aulus Fulvius in Reekwater.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You will? Excellent. Although, It is a bit of a trek. But! If you're sure...\n\nThis message is for the local Magistrate, Aulus Fulvius. He will have need of your talents beyond the lightness of your feet. Of that, I am certain.
InProgressResponse: Just head south for… ages, really. Make sure you have plenty of rations for the journey.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What's this, then? A message all the way from Edengrove? I don't know many who could make that trek in one piece. Consider me impressed.\n\nSince you're here, I believe I can make use of a hardy traveler like yourself.

Title: Clamorous Vox
Description: Collect the pieces to Clamorous Vox for Ranger Madaki to assemble.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There's no better feeling than a musket in your hands, the power of fire, steel, and science.\n\nThere might even be an opportunity to craft a wholly unique firearm, if you're interested.
InProgressResponse: Madaki has the designs. You need only supply the parts.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You've acquired the parts for the Clamorous Vox. \n\nVery well, then you shall have it. A finer musket , the world has never known. Wield it well.

Description: Gather Golden Flintlock from Lost in Periville.

Description: Gather Precision-Engineered Barrel from Corrupted in Greater Tribulation.

Description: Gather Ramrod from Corrupted in Svikin's Stand.

Title: Trigger-Happy
Description: Gather Hair Trigger from Undead in Stone Skull Fort.

Title: Seakissed Wood
Description: Gather Seakissed Wood from Angry Earth in Eridanus.

Title: Heavy is the Base
Description: Gather Shock-Absorbent Base from Corrupted in Scorpius.

Title: Take Stock of the Heart
Description: Gather Impossibly Sturdy Vines from Angry Earth in Malevolence.

Title: Blessing the Rains
Description: Gather the materials necessary to create Torrent, the legendary bow.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, well, if you have sharp eyes, and indeed, you must, if you spotted me here. \n\nThis bow is the mighty Torrent, a bow of legend among the rangers. Acquire these items and it shall be yours.
InProgressResponse: The Torrent would be the envy of any archer in Aeternum.\n\nA weapon without equal, I think.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You've got it all, eh? Otherworldly sinew, ancient bone, an oil coat, and a perfect string for a perfected draw. \n\nTake this bow, the Torrent, and wield it with pride. It's in a class all of its own.

Title: Undead Sagittary
Description: Travel to Periville and collect pieces of Pallid Ash Wood from the Undead.

Title: Bewitched Thumbring
Description: Travel to the Spilaio Cavern and collect fragments of Bewitched Bone from Ancient Guardians.

Title: Sea-crossing Arrow
Description: Travel to the Stone Skull Fort and collect pieces of Seakissed Oak Wood from Pirates.

Title: Vantage Point
Description: Climb the tallest tower in Edengrove, Malevolence, and collect Perfected Hemp String from Alcazarian Archers.

Title: Palm of Hand
Description: Brave Scorpius in Mourningdale and collect a piece of Codex-binding Leather from S'ylanx.

Title: Fine Oil Coat
Description: Travel to the Scorched Mines and collect Scorchvein Oil from Corrupted mineworkers.

Title: Toxic Toxophilite
Description: Travel to the Mangled Heights and collect pieces of Blackened Sinew from Unhallowed Tendrils.

Title: The Remaining Spirit
Description: Travel to Eridanus and collect pieces of Enchanted Azoth Wood from Eridanite Yeoman.

Title: The Reformation
Description: Recover the components needed to create the Greataxe called Reformation, then deliver them to Ranger Madaki in Mountainhome.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I do. The Corrupted call this design 'the Reformation', and though I despise them, I like the name.\n\nGather the components on this list and bring them to Madaki. Then the Reformation will be yours to wield.
InProgressResponse: Have you ever noticed how the Corrupted smell? \n\nIt's like some kind of sulfuric body odor mixed with spoiled fruit. Dreadful.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Here we are, you've acquired the components for the Greataxe. \n\nWell done, this is an axe destined to fell many Corrupted. Wield it with savage fury, {playerName}. Give them something to fear.

Title: A King's Defense
Description: Gather components to create the legendary tower shield Rook's Defense.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I do. Using a shield, and one like this in particular, requires a strategy all of its own.\n\nIt's like a game I once played called 'Chess'; this shield is like the Rook to defend your King.
InProgressResponse: There is no shield I have ever seen as formidable as the Rook's Defense will be.\n\nAssuming you follow through and get Madaki to forge it, that is.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: A masterful game you've played, acquiring these components.\n\n You've earned Rook's Defense, and will doubtlessly wield it with the same impressive valor. Checkmate, indeed.

Title: Chaturanga Opening
Description: The classical opening and setting of the board from the Indian game Chatur that would later inspire Chess. Your opening lies in Malevolence.

Title: White's First Move
Description: In this deadly game of Chess, the ivory pieces move first. Your first move is to Scorpius.

Title: En Passant
Description: The ability of the Pawn to dash forward to the front lines in its first play is a formidable move. Your next move takes you to Eridanus.

Title: Shahnameh's Story
Description: The Persian story of Shahnameh, the reenacting of an epic battle on a Chess board. Your battle continues in Periville.

Title: The Touch-Move Rule
Description: Once a piece has been touched on the Chess board it must be moved. Your next move takes you to Stone Skull Fort.

Title: The Pawn's Promotion
Description: Should a Pawn make it to the other side of the board alive it will be crowned a Queen. Your crowning comes in Caminus.

Title: Castling the King
Description: Castling is a move in Chess wherein the King moves two squares towards a Rook, and then the Rook moves to protect their King’s flank. Castle yourself in Mangled Heights.

Title: Rook's Checkmate
Description: An announcement that the other player's King has been placed in a position of peril. Check the Corrupted of Opulence.
